Vietnamese Stocks: Vinh Son-Song Hinh Hydropower, MT Gas

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-02-14T06:15:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/vietnamese-stocks-vinh-son-song-hinh-hydropower-mt-gas.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Vietnam  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the 11 a.m. local-time close.  The VN Index, the benchmark measure of the Ho Chi Minh City
Stock Exchange, dropped 1.1 percent to 514.05.       Vinh Son-Song Hinh Hydropower Joint Stock Company (VSH VN),
which generates electricity, surged almost 5 percent, the daily
limit, to 12,700 dong, the biggest advance since Jan. 1, 2010.
Vietnam may raise household electricity prices a record 15
percent next month, Vietnam News reported. The increase in the
average household electricity bill would be the largest ever,
the state-run newspaper said today, citing an unidentified
Ministry of Industry and Trade official.  MT Gas Joint-Stock Co. (MTG VN), which distributes natural
gas, dropped 2.4 percent to 8,200 dong, the lowest since Jan. 27.
Crude for March delivery was at $85.52 a barrel, down 6 cents,
in electronic trading on the  New York Mercantile Exchange  at
12:52 p.m. Singapore time. The contract closed at $85.58 on Feb.
11, the lowest since Nov. 30. Prices slid 3.9 percent last week
and are 15 percent higher than a year ago.  To contact the Bloomberg News staff on this story:
